title: Google\Cloud\GkeMultiCloud\V1\Fleet
name: Fleet
description:
Fleet related configuration.

Fleets are a Google Cloud concept for logically organizing clusters, letting you use and manage multi-cluster capabilities and apply consistent policies across your systems. See Anthos Fleets for more details on Anthos multi-cluster capabilities using Fleets.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.gkemulticloud.v1.Fleet

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.project
params.description: Required. The name of the Fleet host project where this cluster will be registered. Project names are formatted as projects/<project-number>.

params.name: data.membership
params.description: Output only. The name of the managed Hub Membership resource associated to this cluster. Membership names are formatted as projects/<project-number>/locations/global/membership/<cluster-id>.
